cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is about reinforcement learning (RL) and its challenges in dealing with context and time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also discusses the use of RL algorithms in gaming environments, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces a new benchmark game, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the use of RL algorithms in robotics, which could place it under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses the use of RL algorithms in control systems, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
